This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on applying visualization techniques to observe how convolutional neural networks can capture different linguistic features in natural language processing tasks. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the decision-making process of the model and how to improve its performance. The paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in image processing tasks, and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks.
